    "We then use the degeneracy to obtain the average probability for each possible single-qubit Pauli error with this signature: ε s /N s. Standard magic-state preparation circuitsHere we describe magic-state preparation circuits with no error suppression that are compared with our error-suppressed scheme described in the main text.In Extended Data Fig. 8a, we show a circuit that prepares an encoded CZ state by, first, preparing a CZ state on two physical qubits and, then, encoding the state such that the Pauli observables of the two qubits of the CZ state can be represented as logical operators of the error-detecting code we encode.",
